        "content": "<p>In proving the sum of two odd natural numbers is even, I got to this goal:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">k</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">l</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">k</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">l</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>but am unsure how to go further.  \"ring\" didn't work, and \"simp\" only got me to 1 + (1 + (2 * k + 2 * l)) = 2 + (2 * k + 2 * l), on which I can't seem to apply add_assoc.  I also tried saying \"import tactic\" at the beginning and that didn't work.</p>",
